---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Music | Ray Weiss"
  description="Music. Ray Weiss recorded as Le Rug, with Sweet Bulbs and Butter The Children before that. Brooklyn projects from a former life."
>
  <main class="px-6 py-24 lg:px-16">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <h1
        class="font-sans text-4xl font-medium tracking-tight text-foreground lg:text-5xl"
      >
        Music
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 font-serif text-lg text-muted">
        Ray recorded as Le Rug. Before that, Sweet Bulbs and Butter The
        Children. The instruments are sold; the catalog is still up.
      </p>

      <div class="prose-body mt-16">
        <p>
          Le Rug was Ray's main music project from Brooklyn for years.
          Full discography at <a href="https://lerug.bandcamp.com/music">lerug.bandcamp.com</a>,
          also on Spotify, Apple Music, and iTunes. The Bandcamp bio
          phrases it as "basically Ray Weiss & Friends." These days the
          focus is on the games and software, but the catalog is still up
          for anyone who wants to dig.
        </p>
        <p>
          CatalogDNA once analyzed this four-hundred-track catalog as its
          development dataset. The canonical structural match came back as
          Pete Burns / Dead or Alive. One of the Le Rug albums is titled <a
            href="https://lerug.bandcamp.com/album/party-with-peter-burns"
            ><em>Party With Peter Burns</em></a
          >, so the album's homage is also its fingerprint. For the full
          recursion, see the <a href="/catalogdna">CatalogDNA page</a>.
        </p>

        <h2>Selected releases</h2>

        <ul>
          <li>
            <a
              href="https://lerug.bandcamp.com/album/party-with-peter-burns"
              ><em>Party With Peter Burns</em></a
            >
          </li>
          <li><em>BOZO DEFENESTRATOR</em></li>
          <li><em>Flabby Wings Ray Weiss</em></li>
          <li><em>C.R.E.E.P.</em></li>
          <li>
            <a href="https://lerug.bandcamp.com/album/bleenex"
              ><em>Bleenex</em></a
            > (2014)
          </li>
          <li>
            <a
              href="https://fleetingyouthrecords.bandcamp.com/album/game-over"
              ><em>Game Over</em></a
            > (Fleeting Youth Records)
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>Full discography at <a href="https://lerug.bandcamp.com/music">lerug.bandcamp.com/music</a>.</p>

        <h2>Previously</h2>

        <h3>Sweet Bulbs</h3>

        <p>
          Indie band, pre-Le Rug. Tyler, the Creator praised Sweet Bulbs
          three times on Twitter, including one tweet about "Junk," the
          song Ray wrote and played guitar on. Archive links below in case
          the originals disappear.
        </p>

        <figure class="mt-8">
          <blockquote>
            "i wish Sweet Bulbs made 'Junk' longer"
          </blockquote>
          <figcaption
            class="mt-2 pl-6 font-mono text-xs not-italic text-subtle"
          >
            @tylerthecreator, on the song Ray wrote and played guitar on
            <span class="mx-2 text-border">·</span>
            <a
              href="https://twitter.com/tylerthecreator/status/165996940948025344"
              class="text-link hover:text-link-hover">original</a
            >
            <span class="mx-2 text-border">·</span>
            <a
              href="https://web.archive.org/web/https://twitter.com/tylerthecreator/status/165996940948025344"
              class="text-link hover:text-link-hover">archive</a
            >
          </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <figure class="mt-8">
          <blockquote>
            "CHECK OUT 'SHAKE APPEAL' BY IGGY POP, AND 'KISSING CLOUDS' BY
            SWEET BULBS"
          </blockquote>
          <figcaption
            class="mt-2 pl-6 font-mono text-xs not-italic text-subtle"
          >
            @tylerthecreator
            <span class="mx-2 text-border">·</span>
            <a
              href="https://twitter.com/tylerthecreator/status/591796727272747008"
              class="text-link hover:text-link-hover">original</a
            >
            <span class="mx-2 text-border">·</span>
            <a
              href="https://web.archive.org/web/https://twitter.com/tylerthecreator/status/591796727272747008"
              class="text-link hover:text-link-hover">archive</a
            >
          </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <figure class="mt-8">
          <blockquote>
            "Sweet Bulbs Is What High School Was Suppose To Sound Like"
          </blockquote>
          <figcaption
            class="mt-2 pl-6 font-mono text-xs not-italic text-subtle"
          >
            @tylerthecreator
            <span class="mx-2 text-border">·</span>
            <a
              href="https://twitter.com/tylerthecreator/status/27707055149"
              class="text-link hover:text-link-hover">original</a
            >
            <span class="mx-2 text-border">·</span>
            <a
              href="https://web.archive.org/web/https://twitter.com/tylerthecreator/status/27707055149"
              class="text-link hover:text-link-hover">archive</a
            >
          </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <h3>Butter The Children</h3>

        <p>
          Brooklyn dreampop band, 2012–2014. Members: Inna Mkrtycheva on
          vocals, Jordyn Blakely on drums (previously of Night Manager), J
          Boxer on bass, and Ray on guitar. Two releases at <a
            href="https://butterthechildren.bandcamp.com"
            >butterthechildren.bandcamp.com</a
          >: the self-titled EP (2012) and <em>True Crime</em> (2014).
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
